# Task Tracker CLI

A simple command-line interface for managing tasks based on the challenge [Task Tracker](https://roadmap.sh/projects/task-tracker)

## Requirements

- Python 3.6+

## Usage

Run the script with Python:

```
python task_cli.py [command] [arguments]
```

## Commands

- Add task: `add "Task description"`
- Update task: `update [id] "New description"`
- Delete task: `delete [id]`
- Mark as in progress: `mark-in-progress [id]`
- Mark as done: `mark-done [id]`
- List all tasks: `list`
- List by status: `list [todo/in-progress/done]`

## Examples

```
python main.py add "Buy groceries"
python main.py update 1 "Buy groceries and cook dinner"
python main.py mark-done 1
python main.py list
```

## Data Storage

Tasks are stored in `tasks.json` in the script's directory.
